<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="C" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Courtesy2" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Courtesy,</orth> vb. (of two syllables), to make a reverence, to bow (in the knees); properly and metaphorically: <bibl n="shak. tmp 1.2.378" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. I, 2, 378</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lll 5.2.221" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL V, 2, 221</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. shr 4.1.95" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. IV, 1, 95</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 3.2.127" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A III, 2, 127</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 2.1.135" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B II, 1, 135</bibl> (Q <emph>make c.</emph>). <bibl n="shak. rom 2.4.58" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. II, 4, 58</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 3.3.55" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. III, 3, 55</bibl>. Followed by <cit><quote>to:</quote> <bibl n="shak. luc 1338" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 1338</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. mv 1.1.13" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. I, 1, 13</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tn 2.5.67" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. II, 5, 67</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 5.2.293" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 V, 2, 293</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 5.3.74" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. V, 3, 74</bibl>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>